.TH _printf 1 "26/03/2025" "version 1.0" user commands
.SH NAME
_printf - format and print data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.#include "main.h"
.TP
.int _printf(const char format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
The _printf function is a custom implementation of the standard printf function, designed to output formatted data to the screen. It mimics the behavior of the traditional printf, but with a more flexible and customized approach to handling various data types and format specifiers.
.SH CONVERSION SPECIFIERS
%c prints a character
.TP
%s prints a string
.TP
%% prints a percent sign
.TP
%d prints a integer
.TP
%i prints a integer
.SH RETURN VALUE
The _printf function returns the total number of characters written if the operation succeeds. In case of an error, it returns -1. If some characters are not accounted for, it returns them as they are.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
#include "main.h"

int main(void)
{
    int year = 2025;

    char grade = 'A';

    charname = "Mynh";

    _printf("Name: %s\n", name);
    _printf("Grade: %c\n", grade);
    _printf("Year: %d\n", year);
    _printf("Literal percent: %%\n");

    return (0);
}
.PP
